<subsection xml:id="subsec-opposite-of-a-vector">
    <title>Opposite of a vector</title>
    <p>
        The opposite of a vector \(\vec{a}\) is denoted by \(-\vec{a}\). It has the same magnitude as \(\vec{a}\) but points in the opposite direction. For example, if \(\vec{a} = (3, 4)\), then \(-\vec{a} = (-3, -4)\).
    </p>
</subsection>